WEBVTT

00:04.250 --> 00:06.036
Previously on Siren...

00:06.040 --> 00:07.280
This will end
very badly.

00:07.290 --> 00:09.167
You need
to find her sister.

00:09.170 --> 00:09.989
[man] Close the glass!

00:13.540 --> 00:15.451
Come on, let's get
out of here, okay?

00:17.290 --> 00:20.327
This part tells us
where you are.

00:20.330 --> 00:21.319
I come back.

00:21.330 --> 00:22.740
Donna, huh?

00:22.750 --> 00:24.069
Hey, are you all right?

00:24.080 --> 00:26.036
I think you might be
in shock.

00:26.040 --> 00:27.075
[Chris, on phone]
Hey, it's me.

00:27.080 --> 00:28.536
Chris?!

00:28.540 --> 00:29.609
Chris, you're alive?!

00:29.620 --> 00:30.609
[Xander] Chris!

00:30.620 --> 00:32.247
He needs help, man.

00:32.250 --> 00:33.740
[shrieks]

00:33.750 --> 00:35.490
[Maddie]
She found her sister.

00:37.290 --> 00:40.327
Home. We lost her.

00:40.330 --> 00:41.877
[Xander] That's the place
where they held Chris.

00:41.880 --> 00:44.075
They're wiping out
all of the evidence.

00:44.080 --> 00:45.069
They'll be coming for him.

00:54.620 --> 00:59.239
[rock music playing]

00:59.250 --> 01:00.615
They taste better cold.

01:00.620 --> 01:02.030
On the house.

01:04.380 --> 01:06.166
Thanks.

01:08.120 --> 01:12.284
[ominous music playing]

01:22.420 --> 01:25.116
[Decker] You're
a hard man to track down.

01:27.710 --> 01:30.452
Glad to see you
looking so healthy.

01:35.380 --> 01:36.574
You remember me?

01:38.670 --> 01:41.241
I saw you at that...
place.

01:43.120 --> 01:45.497
What do you want?

01:45.500 --> 01:48.321
We found that nurse's car
out by Libbey Beach.

01:48.330 --> 01:51.163
When we didn't find you,
we were concerned,

01:51.170 --> 01:54.788
because the woman
you left With,
that nurse, she's...

01:54.790 --> 01:56.917
A nut job?

01:56.920 --> 01:58.160
Unstable.

02:01.290 --> 02:03.576
She's killed several people.

02:05.040 --> 02:07.076
Oh, yeah?

02:07.080 --> 02:09.787
She is extremely violent.

02:09.790 --> 02:12.247
Now, do you know
where she is?

02:12.250 --> 02:14.241
No.

02:14.250 --> 02:18.038
She bolted
as soon as we got
to the beach, okay?

02:18.040 --> 02:20.326
I haven't seen her since.

02:20.330 --> 02:23.072
Glad to hear it.

02:23.080 --> 02:24.206
Yeah.

02:24.210 --> 02:26.201
But if you don't mind,

02:26.210 --> 02:28.246
I want you to tell me

02:28.250 --> 02:30.491
everything
you know about her.

02:32.460 --> 02:36.328
[song in bar]
Let the wall break down

02:37.460 --> 02:40.202
[placid high-pitched calls]

02:51.750 --> 02:53.377
Hey.

02:53.380 --> 02:55.075
You want to tell me
where you've been?

02:55.080 --> 02:58.459
Hey. Uh, I took the boat out
early this morning.

02:58.460 --> 03:00.371
Really? 'Cause I was here
super early,

03:00.380 --> 03:02.200
and there was no boat
and no you.

03:02.210 --> 03:03.871
Okay. Last night.

03:03.880 --> 03:06.701
Female Dragon Fish.

03:07.670 --> 03:09.240
Deep sea species, right?

03:09.250 --> 03:11.115
Lives 2,000 feet down,

03:11.120 --> 03:13.827
so how'd it wind up
floating dead at the surface?

03:13.830 --> 03:16.242
It must have died
near the top.

03:16.250 --> 03:17.706
Where'd you find it?

03:17.710 --> 03:19.530
Out past the Northern Break.

03:19.540 --> 03:20.871
Let me guess.
At the coordinates

03:20.880 --> 03:22.416
where Ryn's tracker dropped out?

03:22.420 --> 03:23.739
Yeah, you know the place.

03:23.750 --> 03:25.320
We've been there
a thousand times.

03:25.330 --> 03:26.706
Yeah, but not alone

03:26.710 --> 03:28.746
and not in the middle
of the night.

03:28.750 --> 03:30.411
It's kind of extreme, dude.

03:30.420 --> 03:32.285
Kind of stupid.

03:32.290 --> 03:35.282
I just want to know if things
are okay where she is.

03:35.290 --> 03:37.326
It's been a month.

03:37.330 --> 03:38.490
She could be anywhere
by now.

03:38.500 --> 03:40.456
Plus, I--

03:42.790 --> 03:44.667
What?

03:44.670 --> 03:47.412
I miss you.

03:47.420 --> 03:49.706
We had this huge thing
happen to us,

03:49.710 --> 03:51.450
and I feel like
we should be closer,

03:54.960 --> 03:57.531
I am, all right?
I'm right here.

03:57.540 --> 03:59.610
Are you?

03:59.620 --> 04:03.112
Yes, I am.

04:03.120 --> 04:04.701
I'm here.

04:09.210 --> 04:11.110
Well, darlin',
I'll send in these labs,

04:11.120 --> 04:12.530
and we should get
a yea or nay

04:12.540 --> 04:14.531
on that medical trial
in the next day or so.

04:14.540 --> 04:15.916
Fingers crossed?

04:19.380 --> 04:22.918
By the by,
I, uh, ran into Ben.

04:22.920 --> 04:25.286
Then you've seen him
more than I have
in the last month.

04:25.290 --> 04:27.326
How did he look?

04:27.330 --> 04:30.117
Whole thing seemed a bit off
to tell you the truth.

04:30.120 --> 04:31.530
Kelly Osterman's
water broke,

04:31.540 --> 04:33.201
so I ended up heading out
to go see them

04:33.210 --> 04:34.575
on-board
their four sleeper.

04:34.580 --> 04:35.990
On the way back in,

04:36.000 --> 04:37.570
I passed Ben heading
out in his trawler.

04:37.580 --> 04:39.787
What was off about that?

04:39.790 --> 04:41.826
Well, it was 3 AM.

04:41.830 --> 04:43.411
Oh.

04:43.420 --> 04:45.536
Was he alone?

04:45.540 --> 04:47.167
Yeah, I'm pretty sure he was.

04:47.170 --> 04:49.741
He wasn't with, you know,
Dale Bishop's girl?

04:49.750 --> 04:51.706
No, Maddie wasn't there.

04:51.710 --> 04:53.575
Thought maybe they were
on the outs actually.

04:53.580 --> 04:55.662
Not that I'm aware of.

04:55.670 --> 04:57.376
What would make you
think that?

04:57.380 --> 04:59.746
About a month ago,
Ben called me twice

04:59.750 --> 05:01.286
to check on
this damsel in distress

05:01.290 --> 05:03.076
he picked up
by the side of the road.

05:03.080 --> 05:04.877
The girl was never there
when I showed up,

05:04.880 --> 05:07.166
either time.

05:07.170 --> 05:10.071
And the second time,
Ben was out cold
on the docks.

05:10.080 --> 05:12.036
I don't know.
Seems to me

05:12.040 --> 05:14.611
the kind of thing
people might break up over.

05:17.080 --> 05:19.492
That's just my boy.

05:19.500 --> 05:22.458
He's always on a mission
to save some...

05:22.460 --> 05:23.870
sad thing.

05:25.170 --> 05:26.410
Aanays,
thank you for that.

05:26.420 --> 05:28.570
Please don't tell him
that I...

05:28.580 --> 05:30.878
Winston, why would I
rat you out?

05:30.880 --> 05:33.667
You're how I know
what my son's up to.

05:41.460 --> 05:43.416
How about we go out,

05:43.420 --> 05:45.160
you know,
like regular people,

05:45.170 --> 05:46.614
take you to dinner?

05:46.620 --> 05:49.532
We can get drunk,
have clumsy sex.

05:49.540 --> 05:51.451
Like regular people?

05:51.460 --> 05:53.166
Yeah,
regular clumsy people.

05:53.170 --> 05:54.205
Mm-hmm.

05:56.620 --> 05:58.372
Yo, guys! Oh!

05:58.380 --> 06:00.666
Okay, whoa.
It's cool. Sorry.

06:00.670 --> 06:03.036
Keep goin' with that.

06:03.040 --> 06:08.535
Oh. There was a nasty accident
on the fishing lanes.

06:08.540 --> 06:10.076
It was a local boat.

06:18.380 --> 06:20.666
Guy's luclq the line
didn't slice off his arm.

06:20.670 --> 06:22.456
How'd it happen?

06:22.460 --> 06:24.371
Oh, last month,‘
we've been fishin'
our asses off,

06:24.380 --> 06:26.610
crews are tired,
guys are gettin' hurt.

06:26.620 --> 06:28.781
The money's great,
but we can't keep this up.

06:28.790 --> 06:30.030
Somebody's gonna die.

06:30.040 --> 06:31.826
You gotta slow down, man.

06:31.830 --> 06:34.617
I mean,
what about the fishing
and game regulations?

06:34.620 --> 06:35.666
Quotas?

06:35.670 --> 06:37.069
I don't know about that,

06:37.080 --> 06:38.570
but right now, they got us
pullin' everything.

06:38.580 --> 06:40.491
Young, old, sick, weird.

06:40.500 --> 06:42.070
NO one seems to care.

06:42.080 --> 06:44.708
I care. You care.

06:44.710 --> 06:46.575
And I know you guys
are just trying
to make a living,

06:46.580 --> 06:48.662
but people
are getting hurt, Xan.

06:48.670 --> 06:50.490
It's not worth it.

06:50.500 --> 06:52.491
-Let's do something
about it.
-[srren]

06:54.500 --> 06:58.288
All right.
All right, I'm done.

06:58.290 --> 07:00.497
All right, find out
what you can from your dad

07:00.500 --> 07:02.707
and the guys on the lanes
and see who's
allowing all this.

07:02.710 --> 07:04.746
I'll figure out what's
happening on the fishery side,

07:04.750 --> 07:06.877
what we're doing
with all this junk fish.

07:06.880 --> 07:09.496
Hey, uh, you mind
if we take this?

07:09.500 --> 07:10.910
Yeah, sure.
It's not good eatin',

07:10.920 --> 07:12.569
but, um,
yeah, have at it.

07:12.580 --> 07:13.911
-Have fun.
-Thanks.

07:16.120 --> 07:18.202
[phone ringing]

07:18.210 --> 07:20.326
[Roberta]
Pownall Seafood.

07:22.040 --> 07:23.826
They told me you were here.

07:23.830 --> 07:25.036
Thanks, Bertie.

07:25.040 --> 07:26.246
Thought I was dreaming.

07:26.250 --> 07:27.535
Ha ha.

07:27.540 --> 07:29.326
Been a little while,
hasn't it?

07:29.330 --> 07:30.786
Yeah, I'm sorry.

07:30.790 --> 07:32.997
Uh, it's been busy
at the Center.

07:33.000 --> 07:35.412
I'd like to think
you're here to say hi
to your own dad,

07:35.420 --> 07:37.911
but I think I know
better than that
by now, don't I?

07:37.920 --> 07:39.740
What's up, kiddo?

07:39.750 --> 07:42.958
Doug told me you were
thinking about bringing me on,

07:42.960 --> 07:44.530
environmental consultant?

07:44.540 --> 07:46.280
I didn't know
he said anything.

07:46.290 --> 07:48.417
Listen, I know
it's not your bag,

07:48.420 --> 07:50.786
but just, before
you make a decision,
just hear me out.

07:50.790 --> 07:51.779
Let's do it.

07:51.790 --> 07:53.746
Really?

07:53.750 --> 07:55.206
You serious? _
You're _not screwm'
With me?

07:55.210 --> 07:57.576
No, I'm in.

07:57.580 --> 07:59.491
Uh... [chuckles]

08:00.620 --> 08:02.781
You don't know.
This is, uh...

08:02.790 --> 08:04.030
This is a big deal to me.

08:04.040 --> 08:07.032
I want to help you
find a better way to fish.

08:07.040 --> 08:09.782
Maybe even make you guys
some more money.

08:09.790 --> 08:10.996
I think we're fishing
just fine,

08:11.000 --> 08:12.490
but if you think
you've got a way

08:12.500 --> 08:14.411
to make me more money,
I'm all ears.

08:14.420 --> 08:16.285
All right,
why don't you come by
tomorrow morning?

08:16.290 --> 08:17.700
See how we do things,

08:17.710 --> 08:19.416
and then we can talk.

08:19.420 --> 08:23.459
And, uh, in the meantime,

08:23.460 --> 08:24.495
uh...

08:26.960 --> 08:28.279
welcome aboard, son.

08:39.620 --> 08:42.202
[door opens and closes]

08:43.670 --> 08:44.659
Hey.

08:44.670 --> 08:45.955
Hey.

08:45.960 --> 08:47.666
How'd it go
with your dad?

08:47.670 --> 08:49.956
Uh, he was real excited
to have me on board.

08:49.960 --> 08:51.279
Ahem...

08:51.290 --> 08:53.201
which kind of sucked,
actually.

08:53.210 --> 08:54.666
Of course it did.

08:54.670 --> 08:56.615
I told you it would.

08:56.620 --> 08:59.453
[Ben] Yeah, I hate
not telling him the truth.

08:59.460 --> 09:00.609
What'd you find out here?

09:00.620 --> 09:03.783
Absence of enzymes
in the digestive tract.

09:03.790 --> 09:04.745
Irregular ammonia levels.

09:04.750 --> 09:06.706
Death by starvation.

09:06.710 --> 09:08.917
[Jerry]
What's up, party people?

09:10.580 --> 09:11.956
-I got dinner.
-Thanks, Jerry.

09:11.960 --> 09:13.666
-[Ben] Thanks.
-Bone app-o—titty.

09:15.830 --> 09:17.491
Sushi? Really, Jer?

09:17.500 --> 09:18.910
Dealer's choice.

09:18.920 --> 09:20.456
I'm outta here. Tchk!

09:22.500 --> 09:23.569
[door closes]

09:23.580 --> 09:25.707
All right.

09:28.500 --> 09:30.491
You know this isn't
what I was thinking

09:30.500 --> 09:33.742
when I said, uh,
"Let's have dinner
like regular people"?

09:33.750 --> 09:35.570
No?

09:35.580 --> 09:36.956
Not exactly.

09:36.960 --> 09:41.249
All right.
How about we skip dinner

09:41.250 --> 09:43.536
and just get straight
to the clumsy sex part?

09:45.790 --> 09:48.111
Works for me.

09:53.790 --> 09:55.667
Yeah, I remember you.

09:55.670 --> 09:56.705
Mm-hmm.

09:58.540 --> 10:00.326
[beeping]

10:01.670 --> 10:03.490
[beeping]

10:03.500 --> 10:04.910
Hey.

10:04.920 --> 10:08.117
[beeping]

10:08.120 --> 10:09.667
It's her tracker.

10:15.040 --> 10:16.826
[Ben]
She's coming back.

10:16.830 --> 10:18.570
She's coming back.

10:18.580 --> 10:20.957
[tracker beeping]

10:27.710 --> 10:29.996
[tracker beeping]

10:35.880 --> 10:37.279
Ben, over here.

10:42.830 --> 10:44.491
[Ben]
Maddie? Look at this.

10:48.920 --> 10:50.035
Think it's her sister?

10:51.120 --> 10:52.280
[Ben] Maybe.

10:53.960 --> 10:55.871
Says she's off the beach.
She's in the woods.

10:55.880 --> 10:56.995
We're just
a little bit behind.

10:57.000 --> 10:58.615
You go.
I'll collect a sample.

10:58.620 --> 11:00.497
[Ben] Okay.

11:00.500 --> 11:03.458
[tracker beeping]

11:09.790 --> 11:11.280
Yes, sir, as far
as he's concerned,

11:11.290 --> 11:13.531
she's just
a deranged nurse.

11:13.540 --> 11:15.610
So the fisherman's no longer
a threat to the project?

11:15.620 --> 11:17.417
[Decker]
If anything, he helped.

11:17.420 --> 11:19.957
He confirmed that she
disappeared at Libbey Beach.

11:19.960 --> 11:23.202
So we mapped
a logical trajectory
off the coast.

11:23.210 --> 11:26.828
We were able to isolate
sound patterns
100 miles offshore.

11:26.830 --> 11:29.537
They match recordings
from our specimen
in Bremerton.

11:29.540 --> 11:30.529
[Harrison]
And you heard it?

11:30.540 --> 11:31.996
She's out there?

11:32.000 --> 11:34.070
[Decker] Or others
very much like her.

11:36.330 --> 11:37.991
Better hope you found her.

11:48.210 --> 11:50.371
[panﬁng]

12:11.040 --> 12:12.371
Stop!

12:14.170 --> 12:16.377
You follow.

12:16.380 --> 12:18.701
Water.

12:18.710 --> 12:20.780
[Donna]
You come back.

12:20.790 --> 12:22.701
You know their words.

12:22.710 --> 12:24.701
[Ryn] We need help...

12:24.710 --> 12:27.873
from the people.

12:27.880 --> 12:29.279
No!

12:29.290 --> 12:30.871
I know people hurt you.

12:30.880 --> 12:33.610
But some are good.

12:33.620 --> 12:34.746
Will help us.

12:49.040 --> 12:50.246
Come.

13:06.960 --> 13:08.780
Put it on.

13:14.460 --> 13:15.996
No!

13:18.460 --> 13:21.111
Wa... ter.

13:21.120 --> 13:23.611
I will stay.

13:23.620 --> 13:25.030
You go.

13:30.500 --> 13:31.489
[hisses]

13:33.500 --> 13:35.570
[tracker beeping]

13:41.960 --> 13:44.326
We need the people.

13:50.210 --> 13:51.325
Now.

13:57.000 --> 13:58.240
[knock on door]

13:58.250 --> 13:59.319
Come in.

14:00.960 --> 14:02.496
[Nina] I've got
the latest rendering.

14:04.120 --> 14:07.169
The engineer designed it
to your specifications, sir.

14:07.170 --> 14:08.706
As requested,
the system allows you to

14:08.710 --> 14:10.996
introduce a sedative
into the water.

14:11.000 --> 14:12.706
[beeping]

14:12.710 --> 14:15.918
One touch will fully
immobilize a specimen.

14:17.080 --> 14:18.741
She told me to assure you

14:18.750 --> 14:20.411
there is no chance
of repeating Bremerton.

14:22.330 --> 14:23.957
Thank you, Nina.

14:31.000 --> 14:35.744
[Siren song echoing]

14:40.500 --> 14:42.070
Any sign of them?

14:42.080 --> 14:43.786
Just this.

14:45.040 --> 14:46.951
Ryn's tracker.

15:00.080 --> 15:02.162
[phone line ringing]

15:02.170 --> 15:04.206
[Helen]
Helen's Antiquities.

15:04.210 --> 15:06.030
Ryn's back.

15:06.040 --> 15:08.417
Why on earth
would she come back?

15:08.420 --> 15:11.071
-We don't know.
-Well, you know
if she shows up here,

15:11.080 --> 15:13.412
I'll send her
right back to the water.

15:13.420 --> 15:14.910
Where are you?

15:14.920 --> 15:16.285
We're on our way
to the Research Center.

15:16.290 --> 15:17.450
Look, if you see her just--

15:17.460 --> 15:18.779
Okay, I'm lockin' up.

15:18.790 --> 15:20.530
I'll see you there.

15:22.420 --> 15:24.115
I didn't really think
she'd go there.

15:24.120 --> 15:26.532
I thought for sure
she'd be at the houseboat.

15:26.540 --> 15:27.666
Me, too.

15:27.670 --> 15:30.161
[phone ringing]

15:32.170 --> 15:33.569
It's your mom.

15:33.580 --> 15:35.070
Hell, no.

15:35.080 --> 15:36.377
I can't.

15:36.380 --> 15:37.449
Worst timing ever.

15:37.460 --> 15:39.075
Yeah.

15:39.080 --> 15:42.072
[phone ringing]

15:42.080 --> 15:44.241
Hello?

15:44.250 --> 15:46.616
Hello, dear.
Elaine Pownall.

15:46.620 --> 15:49.612
Oh. Hi.

15:49.620 --> 15:50.700
[whispering]
It's your mother.

15:50.710 --> 15:52.166
I'm not here.

15:52.170 --> 15:53.660
What a surprise.

15:53.670 --> 15:56.241
It's, uh... It's nice
to hear from you.

15:56.250 --> 15:57.740
[Elaine]
Thank you, dear.

15:57.750 --> 16:00.241
Listen, I was thinking
that maybe it's time

16:00.250 --> 16:02.070
you and I got to know
each other.

16:02.080 --> 16:03.877
I'd like to take you
to lunch.

16:03.880 --> 16:06.417
Wow. Lunch.

16:06.420 --> 16:09.071
Um, that's so nice of you.

16:09.080 --> 16:11.241
How's tomorrow?
Captain's Reef, 1:30?

16:11.250 --> 16:12.319
Does that work for you?

16:12.330 --> 16:14.036
Um, yes. Thanks.

16:14.040 --> 16:16.031
[Elaine]
I'll see you then. Goodbye.

16:16.040 --> 16:18.201
Okay, bye.

16:18.210 --> 16:20.781
So you're going
to lunch with her?

16:20.790 --> 16:22.917
I guess I am.

16:22.920 --> 16:25.115
Wow. Okay.

16:26.420 --> 16:30.322
Fun... for you.

16:30.330 --> 16:32.070
We've barely ever spoken
a word to each other.

16:32.080 --> 16:33.240
She has to stop
and think of my name

16:33.250 --> 16:35.206
every time she sees me.

16:35.210 --> 16:37.075
My advice, cocktails.

16:37.080 --> 16:38.820
Large ones.

16:42.250 --> 16:44.320
[phone ringing]

16:46.080 --> 16:48.662
[Clarence]
All right.

16:48.670 --> 16:51.241
Trespassing call,
north side near the high school.

16:51.250 --> 16:53.115
Couple of randos are running
through baclqards.

16:53.120 --> 16:55.532
You don't need to drive
out there, Clarence.

16:55.540 --> 16:57.280
We're shorthanded.
